11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
14 [11–108.
15 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
16 (2) (i) “Noneconomic damages” means:
17 1. In an action for personal injury, pain, suffering,
18 inconvenience, physical impairment, disfigurement, loss of consortium, or other
19 nonpecuniary injury; and
20 2. In an action for wrongful death, mental anguish,
